# Project Conventions

## Internationalization (i18n)

- The project supports both Chinese (zh) and English (en).
- All user-facing text in console-web and agent-desktop must go through the i18n dictionary — no hardcoded strings.
- API error messages and log messages remain in English.

## Backend Architecture (Go Services)

- All Go backend services (`platform-api`, `session-gateway`, `job-runner`) must follow DDD (Domain-Driven Design) layered architecture:
  - `domain/` — Entities, value objects, repository interfaces. No dependencies on other layers.
  - `repository/` — Implements domain repository interfaces (MySQL/GORM, Redis, etc.).
  - `service/` — Application services that orchestrate domain objects and repositories.
  - `handler/` — HTTP layer (Gin). Parses requests, calls services, returns standardized responses.
  - `dto/` — Data transfer objects for request/response payloads.
- Dependency injection is done manually in `cmd/*/main.go` (repo -> service -> handler).
- Use `gorm.io/gorm` for database operations.
- Use `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` for HTTP routing.
